description: Transactions and Proceedings of the American Philological Association (Open Access Backfiles). ISSN: 0065-9711. Iransactions of the American Philological Association ( TAPA ) is the official research publication of the American Philological Association (APA), a learned society of scholars of the culture and history of the Greek and Roman antiquity. As APA's flagship publication, TAPA reflects the wide range of research undertaken by classicists. Consequently, TAPA includes contributions across the broad spectrum of contemporary methodology from the most traditional to the most innovative.
